WS connect → JWT verified → actorId stored in ConnectionRegistry
       │
       ▼
join-queue → matched → API creates Conversation with GUEST_POLICY
       │
       ▼
ConversationParticipant { actorId: A, personaId: Y }
       │
       ▼
Sends messages → senderParticipantId → renders as "🌿 Silent River"
       │
       ├── [if they leave without registering]
       │       GuestSession expires after 24h → cleanup job deletes
       │       Actor row cascades
       │       Messages remain, persona preserved, participant soft-deleted
       │
       └── [if they register mid-session]
               POST /v1/auth/register (with guest session)
               Actor.userId = newUser.id, Actor.guestSessionId = null
               Actor.type = 'USER'
               GuestSession deleted/invalidated
               New JWT issued { actorId: actor.id }
               WS reconnects with new token — same conversation continues
